column5: Does some one know if there is any launch ramp on Simcoe free of ice where I can launching a 17.5' boat? Had enough waiting for the ice to cover the main lake and it seems it may not happen at all this year....so maybe getting the boat out an early boat season is the solution  Cheers, Ice Fisherman
Yeah!!!!  I like the way you think Emil!!  Stick it to Mother Nature Has been a frustrating season for SW Ontario ice-fishers!
Yep, IBP. Talked with a few guys comming off the lake the other night.
not sure what the tiffin boat launch is like , wanted to see today but did'nt get a chance , i can go check for you a bit later and post backhere if no one eles does
The bay is froze over Ron.
Thanks Brian , tells you how offten i get down town , thanks again for saving me the trip .

Thanks guys...that is what I've heard yesterday but am looking for up to date info as of tonight if  someone knows as it might have changed since yesterday....would hate to drag the boat all the way to IBP only to find out launch is blocked by ice tomorrow morning./  Cheers, Ice Fisherman
That must have been you talking to them when I rolled up Jaspers.... and 'Yes the launch is free of ice and we'll put it to use in the morning....TC and tight lines all...Chuck...
